FBIS3-12006 "drlat060_r_94004" FBIS-LAT-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 27 Mar 1994 Peru Government To Help Mexico Fight Terrorism PY2803203694 Madrid EFE in Spanish 1531 GMT 27 Mar 94 PY2803203694 Madrid EFE Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Lima, 27 Mar (EFE) -- The Peruvian media reported today that the Mexican Government has asked Peru to help their anti-terrorist struggle. The Lima daily EXPRESO reports that within the next few days two National Police Counterterrorism Directorate (Dincote) experts will travel to the Mexican capital with President Alberto Fujimori's authorization. EXPRESO cites high-ranking police sources who state that the officers are Colonel Juan Gonzalez Sandoval and Lieutenant Colonel Alberto Sarmiento Gutierrez. It adds that Gonzalez and Sarmiento will be in Mexico for at least 10 days. Mexican officials want to learn Peruvian methods in facing a possible upsurge of terrorism following the Chiapas rebellion and the death of presidential candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio.
